Patch Set 9: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Hi Sridevi,

The structure of this change looks good, though I think the term "scrub store" needs to be replaced, it is not very clear at all. Perhaps we can resolve the terminology when we meet to discuss https://review.openstack.org/#/c/34801/ ?

I'm confused, though, about the underlying issue here. Why is it invalid to pass in an image location that uses a swift store account identifier instead of credentials?

In the meantime, can you mark your other change that depend on #34801 as work in progress just to help with our accounting purposes? I don't think we can really consider the changes completely until that dependency has been resolved.

Thanks!

Patch Set 9:

Hi Mark,

With the remove-sensitive-data-from-locations patch, we're replacing the swift image locations with the corresponding account refs. But, if we let an end user create images with locations that have the account refs in them, then such locations will be substituted for the actual credentials. This will defeat the purpose of the other patch.

I am marking this as and the other patch as WIP.

Patch Set 9: Work In Progress

Need to decide on the terminology.
And depends on another patch whose approach is still to be decided.
